01:42.336 --> 01:44.303
(indistinct radio chatter)

01:44.305 --> 01:46.939
OFFICER: The car went off the bridge.

01:46.941 --> 01:49.541
Sheriff, we found the third victim.

01:49.543 --> 01:51.710
Was it an accident?

01:52.717 --> 01:55.518
That doesn't look good.

01:55.520 --> 01:57.086
OFFICER: We'll need to drag the river.

01:57.088 --> 01:59.922
Three bodies recovered.

01:59.924 --> 02:02.091
(indistinct chatter continuing)

02:04.662 --> 02:07.596
Confirm three fatalities.

02:07.621 --> 02:10.333
Grayson, Miranda...

02:10.335 --> 02:13.469
and Elena Gilbert.

02:13.471 --> 02:16.372
OFFICER: It's the Gilberts.

02:16.374 --> 02:18.107
That's so sad.

02:18.109 --> 02:21.444
Did you know her?

02:21.446 --> 02:23.613
No, I never met her.

02:25.412 --> 02:27.545
Guess now you never will.

02:34.118 --> 02:39.194
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

02:39.219 --> 02:42.020
(grunting)

02:47.336 --> 02:49.837
Just turn it off.

02:49.839 --> 02:51.238
It's a little bitty

02:51.240 --> 02:54.442
humanity switch right at
the back of your noggin.

02:54.444 --> 02:56.177
I've got big plans for you

02:56.179 --> 02:57.317
and it'll streamline the

02:57.342 --> 02:59.084
whole process if your emotions

02:59.109 --> 03:00.625
aren't riding shotgun.

03:00.650 --> 03:03.584
Come on, Enzo. Room
service is getting cold.

03:03.586 --> 03:06.353
Well, if you're feeling peckish,
don't let me stop you.

03:09.459 --> 03:11.525
(grunts)

03:11.527 --> 03:13.316
Look at Damon over there. He's got

03:13.341 --> 03:15.696
the right idea. He's happy.

03:15.698 --> 03:17.465
Bored, actually.

03:17.467 --> 03:18.833
Just kill him.

03:18.858 --> 03:21.444
SYBIL: In three millennia,
I have a pretty unblemished record

03:21.469 --> 03:23.435
when it comes to controlling men.

03:23.437 --> 03:25.638
50,000 to zero...

03:25.663 --> 03:28.282
Give or take a few Peloponnesians...

03:28.307 --> 03:29.524
And I'm not about to add one

03:29.549 --> 03:30.943
to the loss column just because

03:30.945 --> 03:32.878
he doesn't feel like submitting.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.580
DAMON: Well, he's a tough nut crack.

03:34.582 --> 03:36.849
70 years in a cage'll do that to you,

03:36.874 --> 03:40.296
and you're just building up
his tolerance for torture.

03:40.321 --> 03:42.557
(exhales)

03:42.582 --> 03:44.316
Well I've got a pretty full itinerary,

03:44.318 --> 03:46.017
so I guess we're just gonna have to

03:46.019 --> 03:47.575
move on to Plan “B.”

03:47.600 --> 03:50.522
"B" as in "Bonnie."

03:50.524 --> 03:53.458
Which will be about as
effective as Plan "A."

03:53.483 --> 03:55.278
She means nothing to me.

03:55.303 --> 03:57.395
SYBIL: Is that so?

03:57.397 --> 04:00.198
I guess we'll find out.

04:00.200 --> 04:02.160
- Damon?
- Hmm?

04:02.185 --> 04:06.204
Would you do me a favor
and kill Bonnie Bennett?

04:07.507 --> 04:08.907
Sure.

04:20.887 --> 04:22.320
(chuckles softly)

04:23.759 --> 04:24.693
Surprise!

04:24.718 --> 04:27.201
- Bonnie, what the...
- (laughing)

04:27.226 --> 04:29.466
You are engaged,

04:29.491 --> 04:31.001
and we are celebrating.

04:31.003 --> 04:32.469
(giggles) First,

04:32.494 --> 04:34.161
we're gonna drink too much champagne.

04:34.163 --> 04:35.952
And then, I am taking
you wedding dress shopping.

04:35.976 --> 04:37.694
I know it's a little early,
but you're gonna try on

04:37.718 --> 04:40.326
thousands of dresses before
you find the perfect one,

04:40.351 --> 04:41.655
so we may as well start now.

04:41.680 --> 04:42.980
Bonnie, look,

04:42.982 --> 04:45.781
I love you, and this is amazing,

04:45.806 --> 04:48.118
but you don't have to put on
a happy face for me right now.

04:48.120 --> 04:50.276
I'm not putting it on.

04:50.301 --> 04:52.489
I'm not, I'm happy for you.

04:52.491 --> 04:54.825
I promise. Care, you asked me

04:54.827 --> 04:55.926
to be your bridesmaid

04:55.928 --> 04:57.527
when we were ten years old.

04:57.529 --> 04:59.763
You've been waiting for
this your whole life.

04:59.765 --> 05:01.098
I'm happy for you.

05:01.100 --> 05:02.766
I swear.

05:02.768 --> 05:05.742
(cork hits wall, both yell and laugh)

05:05.767 --> 05:07.804
Okay, but I promise

05:07.806 --> 05:09.606
we are going to find Enzo

05:09.608 --> 05:11.375
and you two are gonna be happy

05:11.377 --> 05:12.809
and you're gonna get
married on the top of

05:12.811 --> 05:15.245
- the Eiffel Tower...
- First things first,

05:15.247 --> 05:16.680
planning your June wedding.

05:16.682 --> 05:17.915
Oh, my God.

05:17.917 --> 05:19.549
Yes! The June wedding!

05:19.551 --> 05:20.817
The June wedding.

05:20.819 --> 05:22.986
(both laugh)

05:22.988 --> 05:25.188
And...

05:26.716 --> 05:29.191
You snuck into my house and
found my old wedding book?

05:29.216 --> 05:32.296
How else was I gonna
out-Caroline-Forbes Caroline Forbes?

05:32.298 --> 05:35.565
Bonnie, this is amazing.

05:35.567 --> 05:37.401
You're amazing.

05:37.403 --> 05:39.569
Thank you.

05:39.571 --> 05:41.705
You're welcome.

05:42.541 --> 05:43.874
I'm getting married!

05:43.876 --> 05:45.075
Yay!

05:45.077 --> 05:47.010
(laughter)

05:47.012 --> 05:49.646
Okay, now that I have a
drink in you, I have to ask.

05:49.648 --> 05:51.260
Mm-hmm?

05:51.285 --> 05:53.750
How did Ric take the news?

05:53.752 --> 05:56.620
Seriously, I'm fine with it.

05:56.622 --> 05:58.188
Yeah, Caroline said you were,

05:58.213 --> 06:00.303
but I just wanted to talk to
you myself, that's all.

06:00.328 --> 06:01.258
(chuckles)

06:01.260 --> 06:03.393
Well, I got two unused
flower girl dresses

06:03.395 --> 06:05.462
I'll sell you cheap.

06:05.464 --> 06:07.130
(scoffs)

06:07.132 --> 06:08.337
- Come on, man.
- (door opens and closes)

06:08.361 --> 06:09.833
Don't make me work this hard to show you

06:09.835 --> 06:11.110
I'm fine with it. Really.

06:11.135 --> 06:12.211
Yeah, he's fine with it.

06:12.236 --> 06:16.707
Hey, uh, why don't you guys go
get set up in the office, okay?

06:16.709 --> 06:18.953
Nanny had the morning off
so I had to work from home.

06:18.978 --> 06:22.679
Got them digging through
miles of arcane siren research.

06:22.681 --> 06:25.084
And what do they, uh,
think that they're doing?

06:25.109 --> 06:26.787
- Earning extra credit.
- Ah.

06:26.789 --> 06:28.756
Helping me with an urgent
publishing deadline.

06:28.758 --> 06:30.724
And how's that deadline coming along?

06:30.726 --> 06:32.026
Caroline said you
might've figured out how

06:32.028 --> 06:33.956
the, uh, Armory captured the siren

06:33.981 --> 06:34.895
in the first place.

06:34.897 --> 06:37.431
Well, if by "figured out"
you mean wild speculation

06:37.433 --> 06:38.866
based on centuries-old

06:38.868 --> 06:41.835
circumstantial evidence...

06:41.837 --> 06:43.684
I think they may have used this.

06:45.406 --> 06:46.772
Would it be going out

06:46.774 --> 06:49.608
on a limb to say that
we stab her with it?

06:49.610 --> 06:51.210
Possibly.

06:51.212 --> 06:52.578
We're dealing with
something that has the power

06:52.580 --> 06:53.912
of mind control.

06:53.914 --> 06:55.180
We get close to her

06:55.182 --> 06:57.049
and we're wrong?

06:58.819 --> 07:00.752
Then we're hers.

07:01.276 --> 07:04.857
♪ Do I look lonely ♪

07:04.859 --> 07:06.658
Let's talk silhouettes.

07:06.660 --> 07:08.427
Focus on A-lines and sheaths.

07:08.429 --> 07:11.096
I'm open to trumpets,
but easy on the volume.

07:11.098 --> 07:12.397
Less dress, more bride.

07:12.399 --> 07:14.066
- Exactly. Thank you.
- Okay.

07:14.068 --> 07:15.634
You're welcome. I'll be right back.

07:17.738 --> 07:20.639
Now, let's get to work
finding you the perfect

07:20.641 --> 07:22.274
maid of honor dress.

07:22.276 --> 07:26.111
Aw, I'd be honored to be your...
maid of honor.

07:26.113 --> 07:27.946
- (chuckles)
- And not just because

07:27.948 --> 07:29.748
my main competition
is in a coma till I die.

07:29.750 --> 07:31.083
(chuckles) Good.

07:31.085 --> 07:32.718
Because I'm going to do everything

07:32.720 --> 07:35.787
within my bridal power
to make sure you and Enzo

07:35.789 --> 07:37.589
live happily ever after.

07:37.591 --> 07:39.157
I've got killer aim...

07:40.461 --> 07:43.595
and no qualms about
rigging the bouquet toss.

07:43.597 --> 07:44.696
(chuckles) You ready?

07:44.698 --> 07:45.697
Yup.

07:45.699 --> 07:48.700
Catch!

07:48.702 --> 07:50.969
Damon, what are you...

07:54.383 --> 07:55.615
Bonnie, run.

07:59.083 --> 08:01.079
Oh, looks like little
brother's getting married, huh?

08:01.081 --> 08:05.183
Consider this my RSVP.

08:05.185 --> 08:07.519
(grunts)

08:08.589 --> 08:10.689
Bonnie?

08:13.093 --> 08:16.828
I can hear your broken little
heart beating, Bonnie.

08:20.467 --> 08:23.001
Oh, poor Bon-bon.

08:23.003 --> 08:27.072
Literally always the bridesmaid.

08:27.074 --> 08:29.775
Never the bride.

08:29.777 --> 08:31.476
(yells)

08:33.480 --> 08:36.248
(grunting)

08:36.850 --> 08:38.582
(groans)

08:50.115 --> 08:51.779
(Damon groans)

08:53.962 --> 08:56.563
So, you got beat up by a girl?

08:56.565 --> 08:59.232
Two girls, if we're counting.

09:03.472 --> 09:04.818
What's so funny?

09:04.843 --> 09:08.708
Just admiring the ladies' craftsmanship.

09:08.710 --> 09:10.143
No.

09:10.145 --> 09:11.412
That look tells me

09:11.437 --> 09:13.230
that you know something I should know,

09:13.255 --> 09:15.081
but you don't want me to know.

09:15.083 --> 09:18.582
And you know how I feel about secrets.

09:21.757 --> 09:23.490
(groans)

09:25.925 --> 09:27.518
Looks like someone forgot to mention

09:27.520 --> 09:29.820
that you and Bonnie
have quite the history.

09:29.822 --> 09:31.956
No wonder your heart wasn't in it.

09:31.958 --> 09:33.757
Well,

09:33.782 --> 09:35.926
we'll see what we can do about that.

09:35.928 --> 09:37.294
Mm...

09:39.499 --> 09:41.966
- Oh, see how scared you are?
- <i>Just leave me alone or I'll scream.</i>

09:41.968 --> 09:43.934
(screams) <i>I know what you are, Damon.</i>

09:43.936 --> 09:46.170
One more move and I'm gonna take you out.

09:46.172 --> 09:49.607
- DAMON: <i>I can make it final.</i>
- BONNIE: <i>Everything that happens</i>

09:49.609 --> 09:51.509
- is his fault.
- DAMON: <i>You know I needed motivation.</i>

09:51.511 --> 09:53.244
- <i>You need motivation.</i>
- Get out!

09:53.246 --> 09:54.845
Whoa.

09:54.847 --> 09:57.314
That's a lot of bad road between you two.

09:57.316 --> 09:58.849
What am I missing?

10:00.086 --> 10:01.852
Oh, wait.

10:01.854 --> 10:03.642
There it is.

10:03.667 --> 10:07.024
Mm-hmm, got it.

10:07.026 --> 10:08.359
BONNIE: I'm sure there are a million people

10:08.361 --> 10:11.462
we'd both rather be with right now,

10:11.464 --> 10:12.730
but...

10:12.732 --> 10:15.332
Couple thousand at most.

10:15.896 --> 10:17.495
Do you think it'll hurt?

10:18.504 --> 10:20.538
DAMON: <i>I don't know.</i>

10:25.585 --> 10:27.418
Mm.

10:28.014 --> 10:29.380
Much better.

10:31.025 --> 10:33.192
Now...

10:35.185 --> 10:37.853
...we have work to do.

10:40.359 --> 10:42.993
Stefan, if Damon wants me dead,
then I'm dead.

10:42.995 --> 10:45.020
Why is he coming after ya?
It makes no sense.

10:45.045 --> 10:47.131
None of it makes sense.

10:47.133 --> 10:49.366
But we're gonna need
weapons, lots of them.

10:50.636 --> 10:53.237
(sighs) The throne is empty.

10:53.239 --> 10:55.330
Right. Yeah, sorry, I was child-proofing.

10:55.355 --> 10:57.251
But the crossbows are still in the library.

10:57.276 --> 10:59.477
Listen, I'm gonna try to track Damon,
and with any luck,

10:59.479 --> 11:01.812
the drone will lead us back to the queen.

11:01.814 --> 11:03.214
And when you find her?

11:04.350 --> 11:06.750
Ric's still working on that part.

11:06.752 --> 11:08.519
Your deadline just got moved up.

11:08.521 --> 11:10.020
You don't have days.

11:10.022 --> 11:12.690
You have hours.

11:17.330 --> 11:19.230
Do you think we can get away

11:19.232 --> 11:21.298
with not inviting Damon to the wedding?

11:21.300 --> 11:23.601
I mean, even if we do save him?

11:24.837 --> 11:26.670
He's gonna be your brother-in-law.

11:26.672 --> 11:28.772
And, likely, Stefan's best man.

11:28.774 --> 11:30.040
Sorry.

11:30.042 --> 11:32.343
(sighs) Fine, fine.

11:32.345 --> 11:34.349
But he is not sitting at the head table.

11:36.582 --> 11:38.516
Where is all the ammo?

11:39.852 --> 11:41.485
(phone ringing, vibrating)

11:41.487 --> 11:44.221
Calling me from your own phone.

11:44.223 --> 11:45.990
Gutsy.

11:45.992 --> 11:47.858
What makes you think I won't
use it to track you down?

11:47.860 --> 11:50.261
No need... I'm at the high school.

11:50.263 --> 11:51.545
Why would you tell me that?

11:51.570 --> 11:53.831
Because I'm gonna need a favor,
little brother.

11:53.833 --> 11:55.833
And what would that be?

11:55.835 --> 11:58.435
Whatever desire you have to save me,

11:58.437 --> 12:02.139
I kind of need that right now.

12:04.043 --> 12:06.076
I'm starting to consider
a destination wedding.

12:06.078 --> 12:07.912
Try finding a Mystic Falls venue

12:07.914 --> 12:10.147
that hasn't been the site
of a horrible atrocity.

12:13.586 --> 12:15.452
Hi, Bonnie.

12:15.454 --> 12:17.054
I'm Sybil.

12:18.206 --> 12:21.040
So glad to finally meet you.

12:31.213 --> 12:33.088
This is really nice work.

12:33.090 --> 12:34.656
Caroline, is it?

12:34.658 --> 12:36.958
I'm not sure about
riding in on the unicorn,

12:36.960 --> 12:40.829
but I love this charmeuse and
the tiara design is exquisite.

12:40.831 --> 12:44.433
Yeah well, I made that in the
sixth grade, so congratulations.

12:44.435 --> 12:47.269
You have the fashion
sense of an 11-year-old.

12:47.271 --> 12:50.572
I just want to know where Bonnie's is.

12:50.574 --> 12:52.441
Scrapbooking's not really my thing.

12:52.443 --> 12:54.343
- What do you want?
- Simple.

12:54.345 --> 12:56.945
I want to know what makes you so special.

12:56.947 --> 12:59.614
What is it about you
that has Enzo and Damon

12:59.616 --> 13:02.484
wrapped around those flawlessly manicured

13:02.486 --> 13:05.620
little fingers? I mean, I get Enzo.

13:05.622 --> 13:07.356
The accent, the star-crossed

13:07.358 --> 13:08.824
witch-vampire thing.

13:08.826 --> 13:10.058
No...

13:10.060 --> 13:11.693
it's the Damon of it all

13:11.695 --> 13:13.762
that has me so stumped.

13:13.764 --> 13:15.597
Did you guys ever...

13:15.599 --> 13:16.832
you know...

13:16.834 --> 13:18.133
No.

13:18.135 --> 13:19.601
All that time, alone in a prison world.

13:19.603 --> 13:21.223
Same day on repeat.

13:21.248 --> 13:24.223
You must've done something to break
up the brain-numbing monotony.

13:24.248 --> 13:25.207
No.

13:25.209 --> 13:26.241
Seriously?

13:26.243 --> 13:28.777
Look, you are gorgeous.

13:28.779 --> 13:30.712
I can admit that, I'm not blind.

13:30.714 --> 13:32.414
And neither is Damon.

13:32.416 --> 13:34.383
Who, in case you haven't noticed, ladies,

13:34.385 --> 13:36.351
is scorching. I mean... (scoffs)

13:36.353 --> 13:38.854
...you can't spell Damon without "damn."

13:38.856 --> 13:41.089
Strictly platonic?

13:41.091 --> 13:42.624
Really?

13:42.626 --> 13:44.025
Wow.

13:44.027 --> 13:45.427
Good for you.

13:45.429 --> 13:47.028
That doesn't explain how you inspire

13:47.030 --> 13:48.864
so much devotion in two men

13:48.866 --> 13:50.098
who are supposed to be

13:50.100 --> 13:52.868
completely devoted to me.

13:52.870 --> 13:55.103
So why don't you sit down
and we'll have a little

13:55.105 --> 13:56.538
heart-to-heart?

13:57.975 --> 13:59.307
I can make you.

14:00.144 --> 14:02.277
But it's excruciatingly painful.

14:02.279 --> 14:05.547
And it'll mess up your hair.

14:07.751 --> 14:10.288
GEORGIE: There's nothing
in the historical records

14:10.313 --> 14:11.520
about a weapon like this.

14:11.522 --> 14:13.021
Please tell me there's a "but".

14:13.023 --> 14:14.423
But I have a theory.

14:14.425 --> 14:15.891
Okay. So...

14:15.893 --> 14:17.859
assuming that the symbol etched into it

14:17.861 --> 14:20.595
has a connection to hell,

14:20.597 --> 14:22.917
what's the first thing you
think of when you think of hell?

14:24.001 --> 14:25.600
The devil, right?

14:25.602 --> 14:27.102
And what's the most common
visual representation

14:27.104 --> 14:28.370
of the devil?

14:28.372 --> 14:29.783
Uh, a man in a red suit.

14:29.808 --> 14:31.606
Pointy tail.

14:31.608 --> 14:34.476
- With a pitchfork.
- Ding-ding-ding.

14:34.478 --> 14:37.617
Okay, in the medieval tradition,
the pitchfork symbolized

14:37.642 --> 14:39.481
the separation of the
wheat from the chaff.

14:39.483 --> 14:41.216
Which was obviously a metaphor

14:41.218 --> 14:43.185
for good souls going to
heaven and garbage souls going

14:43.187 --> 14:45.454
to the big fiery basement.

14:45.456 --> 14:47.088
Well, shouldn't that have three tines?

14:47.090 --> 14:50.158
Not in 2200 B.C. when it was forged.

14:50.160 --> 14:52.394
The soil around the
Mediterranean was rocky.

14:52.396 --> 14:55.464
So their pitchforks only had two.

14:55.466 --> 14:57.032
Okay, well that's all very interesting,

14:57.034 --> 14:58.300
but that doesn't tell us anything

14:58.302 --> 14:59.568
about its connection to the sirens,

14:59.570 --> 15:01.937
- how we'd use it...
- We?

15:01.939 --> 15:03.738
Why would we use it? Like this is real?

15:03.740 --> 15:05.607
As in some sort of magical weapon?

15:05.609 --> 15:07.108
- Come on, you know what I mean.
- No.

15:07.110 --> 15:09.044
Actually, I don't.
You sure this is for a book?

15:09.046 --> 15:10.986
'Cause you're treating it
like lives are at stake.

15:11.010 --> 15:12.777
Worse.

15:14.785 --> 15:17.285
Tenure, okay?

15:17.287 --> 15:20.222
Now, keep digging.

15:23.760 --> 15:26.928
Look if this is all some
sort of an elaborate trap,

15:26.930 --> 15:30.065
we might as well skip to the
part where you spring it.

15:30.067 --> 15:32.601
No trap, elaborate or otherwise.

15:32.603 --> 15:35.170
I just need your help.

15:35.172 --> 15:37.739
With what?

15:39.009 --> 15:40.951
I can't tell you.

15:40.976 --> 15:43.623
No, I mean I literally can't tell you.

15:43.648 --> 15:46.882
I can't physically make
myself form the words.

15:46.884 --> 15:49.784
That's the thing about Sybil,
she's not big on free will.

15:49.786 --> 15:52.153
She kind of LoJacked my brain.

15:52.155 --> 15:53.889
Whenever I try and form the words

15:53.891 --> 15:55.156
to tell you what's going on,

15:55.158 --> 15:57.292
it just comes out applesauce penguin.

15:57.294 --> 16:00.128
Well, if you cant tell me how to
save you, then I'm at a loss,

16:00.130 --> 16:03.064
because I'm running out of ways
to pull you back from the brink.

16:03.066 --> 16:04.917
Sounds suspiciously like
someone's given up.

16:04.942 --> 16:05.734
Not yet.

16:05.736 --> 16:07.569
But I'm not about to let Elena wake up

16:07.571 --> 16:09.558
to find out you murdered her best friend.

16:09.583 --> 16:11.406
This isn't for Bonnie.

16:11.408 --> 16:13.742
Then, who's it for?

16:14.978 --> 16:17.045
♪ ♪

16:24.621 --> 16:27.989
So, Bonnie, what's your secret?

16:27.991 --> 16:30.458
What did Damon and Enzo see in you?

16:30.460 --> 16:32.727
I have no idea.

16:32.729 --> 16:34.262
Oh, come on, Bonnie.

16:34.264 --> 16:36.831
- Surely you can think of something.
- You know,

16:36.833 --> 16:39.768
whatever you're trying to do here,
it's not going to work.

16:39.770 --> 16:41.803
You're not going to get what you want.

16:41.805 --> 16:44.039
Something you should know about Bonnie

16:44.041 --> 16:46.641
is that she is fiercely loyal

16:46.643 --> 16:49.778
and she would do anything
for the people she loves.

16:52.241 --> 16:54.247
Really?

16:55.419 --> 16:58.286
Now that is something we can work with.

16:58.288 --> 17:01.356
So you would do anything
for Damon and Enzo?

17:01.358 --> 17:03.515
Like, <i>anything</i> anything?

17:03.540 --> 17:06.094
I mean, how far would you really go?

17:07.130 --> 17:09.731
What if you had to choose between them?

17:09.733 --> 17:11.833
(chuckles)

17:13.036 --> 17:14.669
Here's the thing, ladies.

17:14.671 --> 17:17.305
I need two loyal soldiers,

17:17.307 --> 17:20.508
and these two can't seem to
cut loose from their ties

17:20.510 --> 17:21.910
to the past.

17:21.912 --> 17:23.877
It's working my last nerve.

17:23.880 --> 17:25.113
So, I realized,

17:25.115 --> 17:26.881
I really only need one of them.

17:26.883 --> 17:28.550
The other will die

17:28.551 --> 17:32.354
and live an eternity of
darkness and pain.

17:32.356 --> 17:34.089
(chuckles)

17:34.091 --> 17:35.790
So...

17:35.792 --> 17:37.726
Bonnie gets to choose.

17:38.629 --> 17:40.328
- You're crazy.
- No.

17:40.330 --> 17:42.197
I'm just very old,

17:42.199 --> 17:45.834
very set in my ways and very annoyed.

17:46.970 --> 17:49.270
Choose.

17:49.272 --> 17:52.707
I get it. You're jealous.

17:52.709 --> 17:55.443
You see a love that you didn't
have to siren someone into.

17:55.445 --> 17:58.780
A love that isn't all about you.
You're threatened.

17:58.782 --> 18:00.515
So, naturally you have to destroy it

18:00.517 --> 18:02.517
in the most sadistic game

18:02.519 --> 18:04.486
you can imagine. Forget it.

18:04.488 --> 18:06.154
Not playing.

18:06.156 --> 18:07.589
You're no fun.

18:07.591 --> 18:09.324
You know what <i>was</i> fun?

18:09.326 --> 18:11.026
Ancient Rome.

18:11.028 --> 18:13.028
(chuckles)

18:13.030 --> 18:14.863
The Colosseum.

18:14.865 --> 18:15.897
Gladiators.

18:15.899 --> 18:18.133
Sweaty, oiled-up men

18:18.135 --> 18:20.068
hurling themselves at each other.

18:20.093 --> 18:21.713
So hot.

18:21.738 --> 18:25.206
You'll see what I mean soon enough.

18:26.109 --> 18:28.143
In exactly 12 minutes,

18:28.145 --> 18:30.779
<i>Damon and Enzo will fight to the death.</i>

18:30.781 --> 18:33.815
<i>They don't have a choice.</i>

18:33.817 --> 18:36.584
<i>I've willed it so.</i>

18:36.586 --> 18:38.987
One of them will lose.

18:38.989 --> 18:40.955
So, if you're not gonna choose,

18:40.957 --> 18:43.024
<i>then I guess we'll just let the boys</i>

18:43.026 --> 18:46.194
<i>settle it amongst themselves.</i>

18:51.048 --> 18:53.015
ALARIC: All right,
I didn't cut them into star shapes

18:53.017 --> 18:55.417
like Seline does,
but I've got some really cool

18:55.419 --> 18:57.727
- square shapes for you.
- JOSIE: I had it first.

18:57.752 --> 18:59.154
- But I had it first. I had it.
- Girls.

18:59.156 --> 19:00.489
Lizzie...

19:00.491 --> 19:02.442
Put that down, right now.

19:02.467 --> 19:03.485
But Daddy, I had it first.

19:03.487 --> 19:04.686
I said drop it.

19:04.688 --> 19:05.854
(clatters, reverberates)

19:05.856 --> 19:08.990
(screaming) Daddy, make it stop!

19:08.992 --> 19:11.059
Daddy! Daddy!

19:11.061 --> 19:12.293
(reverberating stops)

19:12.295 --> 19:13.928
ALARIC: Shh...

19:13.930 --> 19:16.765
Oh, my God. Are they okay?
Did they cut themselves?

19:16.790 --> 19:18.229
I'm so sorry I left that out.

19:18.231 --> 19:19.797
It's okay.

19:19.799 --> 19:22.133
You were right about that
being a pitchfork.

19:22.135 --> 19:23.367
Literally.

19:23.369 --> 19:24.769
Emphasis on "pitch."

19:25.772 --> 19:27.939
It's a tuning fork.

19:32.979 --> 19:35.146
(soft beeping)

19:38.985 --> 19:42.053
Why does the car keep
making that infernal noise?

19:42.055 --> 19:45.556
Oh, it's reminding you
to put your seatbelt on.

19:45.558 --> 19:48.559
Well, you can remind
it that I'm immortal.

19:48.561 --> 19:50.628
And this is how you
choose to spend that gift.

19:50.630 --> 19:54.298
You just escaped over
200 years of captivity.

19:54.300 --> 19:56.501
Why aren't you on a beach in Saint-Tropez

19:56.503 --> 20:00.171
sirening Channing Tatum
to give you foot massages?

20:01.274 --> 20:02.974
♪ ♪

20:02.976 --> 20:05.143
No offense, but you got to admit

20:05.145 --> 20:06.477
that seems a little small for

20:06.479 --> 20:08.846
a mythological creature of your stature.

20:08.848 --> 20:10.314
That's only 'cause you don't know what

20:10.316 --> 20:12.350
awesomeness awaits you.

20:12.352 --> 20:13.651
Now step on it.

20:13.653 --> 20:16.187
We don't want to miss round one.

20:18.158 --> 20:20.324
(phone chimes)

20:22.362 --> 20:23.694
That's what this is about?

20:23.696 --> 20:26.898
You two fight each other to the death?

20:26.900 --> 20:28.900
Well, I don't know about
the "each other" part.

20:28.902 --> 20:31.169
Which is why I brought
you along as a second.

20:31.171 --> 20:33.704
So you don't want me to
help you fight Sybil.

20:33.706 --> 20:35.706
You actually want me to
help you fight Enzo?

20:35.708 --> 20:37.775
- Yeah, hardly a fair fight at that.
- Hey, man.

20:37.777 --> 20:39.677
Nowhere in Sybil's fine print did it say

20:39.679 --> 20:41.312
anything at all about no backup.

20:41.314 --> 20:43.614
And it's not my fault you
don't have any friends

20:43.616 --> 20:45.416
- to stand up for you.
- Oh, yes, yes.

20:45.418 --> 20:48.452
How naive of me to think
that you were my friend.

20:48.454 --> 20:50.087
I tried to be your friend, Enzo.

20:50.089 --> 20:51.355
Tried to convince you to give yourself

20:51.357 --> 20:53.658
- over to Sybil.
- Hey. If Enzo

20:53.660 --> 20:56.027
can fight this, why can't you, Damon?

20:56.029 --> 20:58.629
'Cause it's pointless, Stefan.

20:58.631 --> 21:00.431
We are in this mess

21:00.433 --> 21:02.066
because he refuses to accept that.

21:02.068 --> 21:03.768
But if he'd just sign over his pink slip

21:03.770 --> 21:06.304
to Sybil, we wouldn't be here.

21:06.306 --> 21:09.640
You can't kill Enzo.
Bonnie would never forgive you.

21:09.642 --> 21:12.043
Oh, don't bother, mate.
She's been messing around

21:12.045 --> 21:14.045
in the recesses of his brain,

21:14.047 --> 21:16.547
toying with the safe
places in his subconscious.

21:16.549 --> 21:18.449
Lord only knows the damage she's done.

21:18.451 --> 21:20.318
("Missile" by Dorothy begins)

21:20.320 --> 21:22.587
SYBIL: <i>Five minutes.</i>

21:22.589 --> 21:24.222
This is so exciting.

21:24.224 --> 21:27.091
Oh, come on, what happened to all that

21:27.093 --> 21:28.659
sassy backtalk?

21:28.661 --> 21:30.228
Oh, right.

21:30.230 --> 21:32.029
It's probably easier to talk tough

21:32.031 --> 21:34.432
when you had your magic to back it up.

21:34.434 --> 21:35.533
What's wrong?

21:35.535 --> 21:38.636
Somebody feeling powerless right now?

21:38.638 --> 21:40.771
But here's the ray of sunshine.

21:40.773 --> 21:44.575
You actually have <i>all</i> the power.

21:44.577 --> 21:47.378
Just say the word, and you can decide

21:47.380 --> 21:50.081
who gets to live and who gets to spend

21:50.083 --> 21:54.151
the rest of eternity in
never-ending emotional torment.

21:54.153 --> 21:55.953
Oh, you guys know about that,

21:55.955 --> 21:57.488
right?

21:57.490 --> 21:59.790
They're homicidal monsters.

21:59.792 --> 22:02.994
They have done the
worst things imaginable.

22:02.996 --> 22:05.062
Where do you <i>think</i>
they're gonna end up?

22:05.064 --> 22:07.164
Some cloud-filled afterlife?

22:07.166 --> 22:09.166
(laughs): No.

22:09.168 --> 22:11.869
They're going to the other place,

22:11.871 --> 22:13.337
where all they will know

22:13.339 --> 22:15.139
is loneliness and despair

22:15.141 --> 22:17.475
forever and ever and ever.

22:17.477 --> 22:19.543
DAMON: <i>You two forget that</i>

22:19.545 --> 22:21.979
I don't care about anything anymore.

22:21.981 --> 22:23.514
♪ Love is destruction ♪

22:23.516 --> 22:25.683
I'm just trying to stay alive.

22:25.685 --> 22:27.184
He and I both know

22:27.186 --> 22:29.020
what awaits us if we don't.

22:29.022 --> 22:30.521
♪ I am a missile ♪

22:30.523 --> 22:32.390
SYBIL: <i>What about you, Caroline?</i>

22:32.392 --> 22:34.492
What do you think Bonnie should do?

22:34.494 --> 22:36.294
(grunts)

22:36.296 --> 22:37.461
(whooshing)

22:37.463 --> 22:38.729
(whooshing stops)

22:38.731 --> 22:39.964
(laughs)

22:39.966 --> 22:41.899
Oh, you think Stefan is

22:41.901 --> 22:43.768
gonna swoop in and save Bonnie

22:43.770 --> 22:46.203
from having to make such
an untenable choice.

22:46.205 --> 22:47.772
(laughs)

22:47.774 --> 22:50.141
<i>That's putting a lot of
faith in your fiancé.</i>

22:50.166 --> 22:52.310
Enzo... you need to run.

22:52.312 --> 22:53.611
Afraid I don't have enough free will

22:53.613 --> 22:54.779
left in the tank for that.

22:54.781 --> 22:56.547
Stefan...

22:56.549 --> 22:57.982
what are you doing?

22:57.984 --> 23:00.217
I didn't bring you here
to be Switzerland.

23:00.219 --> 23:02.920
SYBIL: <i>When Damon and Enzo
start tearing each other apart,</i>

23:02.922 --> 23:07.391
do you really think Stefan is
gonna let Enzo kill his brother?

23:07.393 --> 23:10.294
No. He's gonna choose Damon.

23:10.296 --> 23:12.897
DAMON: <i>I brought you here
because you are my brother.</i>

23:12.899 --> 23:14.198
When that clock strikes 3:00,

23:14.200 --> 23:15.232
I'm gonna be counting on you

23:15.234 --> 23:16.434
to remember that.

23:16.436 --> 23:17.635
SYBIL: <i>Aw.</i>

23:17.637 --> 23:19.370
<i>Poor Enzo.</i>

23:19.372 --> 23:21.038
Nobody's choosing him.

23:21.040 --> 23:23.507
You're not even choosing him, Bonnie.

23:23.509 --> 23:25.609
Are you just gonna sit there

23:25.611 --> 23:28.546
and allow Enzo to die?

23:28.548 --> 23:30.665
No.

23:30.690 --> 23:32.616
(Bonnie grunts, tires screech)

23:32.618 --> 23:35.086
(yells)

23:36.356 --> 23:37.922
You okay?

23:37.924 --> 23:39.557
Oh. Yeah.

23:39.559 --> 23:41.333
She's not dead.

23:42.729 --> 23:45.296
Guess now she has to walk.

23:54.313 --> 23:56.093
(alarm sounds)

23:59.375 --> 24:02.086
(grunting)

24:19.273 --> 24:20.772
I am not

24:20.774 --> 24:22.274
- letting you two kill each other.
- (grunts)

24:22.276 --> 24:25.210
You think I want this?

24:25.212 --> 24:26.778
He's not gonna stop, Stefan.

24:26.780 --> 24:28.180
But I will put him down if I have to.

24:28.182 --> 24:30.649
If you get in my way,
I will kill you, too.

24:32.553 --> 24:34.186
(fighting, grunting)

24:34.188 --> 24:36.755
(high-pitched tone sounding)

24:38.659 --> 24:41.093
♪ ♪

24:51.305 --> 24:54.172
(woman vocalizing)

25:07.121 --> 25:10.889
We'll make it in time.

25:10.891 --> 25:13.358
No, Sybil's right.

25:13.360 --> 25:17.729
Stefan's gonna protect
Damon no matter what.

25:17.731 --> 25:19.131
I can't help him.

25:19.133 --> 25:21.199
I have no power.

25:21.201 --> 25:24.503
She's right.

25:24.505 --> 25:26.738
There is no one who can fight for him.

25:32.012 --> 25:33.612
All right, kids are at the neighbors',

25:33.614 --> 25:35.380
Seline should be here in a half hour.

25:35.382 --> 25:36.948
Tell her there's something
I have to take care of.

25:36.950 --> 25:39.341
Yeah? There a giant piano
out of tune somewhere?

25:39.366 --> 25:40.427
You know, Ric,

25:40.452 --> 25:41.841
I could actually help you a lot better

25:41.843 --> 25:44.677
with your "book," or
whatever that's code for,

25:44.679 --> 25:46.230
if you just told me
what's really going on.

25:46.254 --> 25:48.414
You're right. I'm actually
taking this to go do battle

25:48.416 --> 25:51.417
with a mythical creature
from the ancient world.

25:51.419 --> 25:53.419
Wish me luck.

25:53.421 --> 25:54.987
(door closes)

25:59.727 --> 26:01.360
(grunts)

26:09.070 --> 26:10.703
(yells)

26:11.272 --> 26:13.472
(groaning)

26:18.646 --> 26:20.679
(both grunting)

26:23.351 --> 26:26.018
(groans)

26:27.622 --> 26:30.556
(squishing sound, Damon straining)

26:30.558 --> 26:32.324
Little help over here, brother.

26:40.598 --> 26:43.569
- I can't let you do that.
- Caroline, stay out of this.

26:43.571 --> 26:45.832
I promised Bonnie.

26:45.857 --> 26:48.407
(bones crack, body thuds on floor)

26:48.409 --> 26:51.110
(grunts, body thuds on floor)

26:57.084 --> 26:59.552
(grunting)

26:59.554 --> 27:01.887
(Enzo yells)

27:01.889 --> 27:04.857
(squishing sound, Enzo groaning)

27:06.227 --> 27:07.493
God...

27:07.495 --> 27:08.894
BONNIE: Damon, no.

27:08.896 --> 27:10.262
Damon?

27:10.264 --> 27:11.664
Please.

27:11.666 --> 27:13.899
Please fight through this.

27:13.901 --> 27:15.501
(squishing)

27:15.503 --> 27:16.781
(continues groaning)

27:16.806 --> 27:18.637
I know you can.

27:19.083 --> 27:21.150
Damon, he's your friend.

27:22.523 --> 27:24.289
Stop!

27:24.291 --> 27:26.792
SYBIL: He can't.

27:26.794 --> 27:29.161
The only one that can stop him is you.

27:29.163 --> 27:30.228
Choose.

27:30.230 --> 27:32.230
(both groaning)

27:33.400 --> 27:35.067
Please, Damon. Damon!

27:35.069 --> 27:36.735
Damon, don't make me do this.

27:36.737 --> 27:40.205
Sorry, not sorry, Bon.

27:40.207 --> 27:42.274
(cries out)

27:42.276 --> 27:44.009
I choose Enzo!

27:47.347 --> 27:49.214
- What?
- SYBIL: Damon?

27:49.216 --> 27:52.184
Kindly remove your hand,
without the gentleman's

27:52.186 --> 27:53.752
heart in it.

27:55.789 --> 27:57.122
(exhales)

27:57.124 --> 27:58.657
(Enzo groans)

28:03.363 --> 28:05.430
DAMON: No. Bonnie,

28:05.432 --> 28:07.699
don't do this to me.

28:07.701 --> 28:11.103
I know that somewhere deep down,

28:11.105 --> 28:13.505
there's still some part of you left.

28:13.507 --> 28:15.907
She couldn't have stripped it all away.

28:15.909 --> 28:17.669
You're...

28:17.694 --> 28:20.846
obnoxiously too stubborn
to let that happen.

28:22.416 --> 28:24.349
I know my friend is still in there,

28:24.351 --> 28:25.984
and I'm gonna have to live with that.

28:29.189 --> 28:32.357
I just can't let him die.

28:32.359 --> 28:35.260
I choose Enzo.

28:36.964 --> 28:40.365
Oof, I'm getting all weepy.

28:40.367 --> 28:41.900
So touching.

28:41.902 --> 28:43.368
So raw.

28:43.370 --> 28:45.237
DAMON: I know where I'm going when I die.

28:45.239 --> 28:47.806
You can't send me there.

28:47.808 --> 28:50.041
I'll fight every one of you.

28:50.043 --> 28:51.610
SYBIL: Hmm.

28:51.612 --> 28:54.813
So Bonnie can't live without Enzo.

28:54.815 --> 28:58.183
And clearly,
Stefan can't live without Damon.

28:58.185 --> 29:01.386
But nobody's bothered
to ask me what I want.

29:01.388 --> 29:03.054
You're the only one

29:03.056 --> 29:05.490
that's truly committed
around here, Damon.

29:05.492 --> 29:07.025
You're an asset.

29:07.027 --> 29:09.327
Enzo's nothing but a burden.

29:09.329 --> 29:10.495
So...

29:10.497 --> 29:12.831
I guess my only real problem

29:12.833 --> 29:14.800
is with you, Bonnie.

29:16.103 --> 29:18.570
You chose wrong.

29:18.572 --> 29:21.506
Which is why I'm gonna
have Damon kill you.

29:21.508 --> 29:23.475
What?

29:23.477 --> 29:24.910
(giggles)

29:24.912 --> 29:27.412
Damon kills Bonnie, I'll kill you,

29:27.414 --> 29:29.781
and then we can all
get on with our lives.

29:29.783 --> 29:34.186
Unless... you give me what I want.

29:35.722 --> 29:38.857
Turn off your humanity,
pledge your loyalty to me,

29:38.859 --> 29:41.193
and then we can all go home happy.

29:41.195 --> 29:43.195
Pinkie swear.

29:43.197 --> 29:45.397
Don't trust her.

29:45.399 --> 29:47.165
(soft chuckle)

29:47.167 --> 29:49.334
Sorry, love.

29:49.336 --> 29:50.761
I'm not seeing many other options.

29:50.786 --> 29:52.170
BONNIE: Enzo.

29:52.172 --> 29:53.839
Don't.

29:53.841 --> 29:56.007
Yes, Enzo, do.

29:56.009 --> 29:57.876
You know you want to.

29:57.878 --> 30:00.378
Come on, this is mercy.

30:00.380 --> 30:02.447
You've seen what happens when you die.

30:02.449 --> 30:05.283
What if your precious
Bonnie is due the same fate?

30:05.285 --> 30:07.619
Save yourself.

30:07.621 --> 30:10.689
Save your one true love.

30:10.691 --> 30:12.624
Do it.

30:16.063 --> 30:19.000
- Bonnie, Bonnie...
- What are you doing?

30:19.025 --> 30:22.267
...if anyone can pull me back
from the precipice, it's you.

30:22.269 --> 30:23.535
I know you can.

30:23.537 --> 30:24.803
No.

30:24.805 --> 30:26.705
No.

30:26.707 --> 30:28.440
No, no.

30:28.442 --> 30:30.575
No.

30:38.585 --> 30:40.719
No.

30:40.721 --> 30:42.954
No, no.

30:57.337 --> 31:00.906
(giggles)

31:00.908 --> 31:02.307
Finally.

31:02.309 --> 31:04.609
Now, was that so hard?

31:06.200 --> 31:07.946
Oh, one last thing,

31:07.948 --> 31:09.281
would you mind if I took back

31:09.283 --> 31:11.516
my promise to spare Bonnie's life?

31:13.020 --> 31:15.587
No objections here.

31:15.589 --> 31:17.856
(soft gasp)

31:17.858 --> 31:19.991
You're the best.

31:21.128 --> 31:22.327
Bonnie,

31:22.329 --> 31:24.562
I'm gonna count down from ten,

31:24.564 --> 31:27.966
and then I'm gonna let Damon
finish what he started.

31:27.968 --> 31:29.801
Ten.

31:29.803 --> 31:31.369
Nine.

31:31.371 --> 31:32.737
Enzo, you sure you don't mind

31:32.739 --> 31:34.973
if Damon rips your girlfriend to shreds?

31:34.975 --> 31:36.508
- No.
- (gasps)

31:36.510 --> 31:38.176
Eight.

31:38.178 --> 31:40.145
So much for your indomitable

31:40.147 --> 31:41.546
love.

31:41.548 --> 31:43.148
Seven. Looks like

31:43.150 --> 31:44.649
Enzo's not gonna help you.

31:44.651 --> 31:46.384
Six.

31:46.386 --> 31:51.089
Pretty sure Stefan and Caroline
won't be much help, either.

31:51.091 --> 31:54.326
Five. Bonnie, you really

31:54.328 --> 31:57.729
should be running now. Four.

32:09.450 --> 32:11.751
(gasps)

32:13.388 --> 32:15.855
(yells) Damon, Stop!

32:15.857 --> 32:18.224
Please.

32:18.226 --> 32:21.660
You've got one last decision
to make, Bonnie.

32:22.797 --> 32:25.264
It's a multiple choice.

32:25.266 --> 32:27.166
Neck snap,

32:27.168 --> 32:29.568
heart rip, or just good,

32:29.570 --> 32:31.515
old-fashioned tear your throat out?

32:31.540 --> 32:33.472
(tires squeal, thudding)

32:34.909 --> 32:36.809
SYBIL: I don't know who

32:36.811 --> 32:37.877
you are, but...

32:37.879 --> 32:39.912
(high-pitched tone echoes)

32:39.914 --> 32:42.782
(yelling)

32:51.926 --> 32:53.125
(yells)

32:54.923 --> 32:57.457
(groans)

33:02.036 --> 33:03.569
(bones cracking)

33:03.571 --> 33:05.304
Damon, it's over.

33:05.306 --> 33:06.672
You're free now.

33:06.674 --> 33:08.140
I wish that were the case, Stefan,

33:08.142 --> 33:10.176
but my work with her is
just getting started.

33:10.178 --> 33:11.677
What work?

33:11.679 --> 33:13.913
What does she want with you?

33:13.915 --> 33:17.149
Applesauce penguin, brother.

33:19.420 --> 33:21.554
(car engine starts)

33:21.556 --> 33:24.123
(engine revving)

33:28.963 --> 33:31.530
(crickets chirping)

33:34.954 --> 33:37.655
Maybe now we'll get some answers.

33:40.150 --> 33:42.517
You sure you can handle Enzo?

33:42.519 --> 33:44.686
I'll be fine.

33:44.688 --> 33:48.112
You know, if you need my help
with getting him to the cabin...

33:48.137 --> 33:49.858
I said I'll be fine.

33:49.860 --> 33:51.993
Okay.

33:51.995 --> 33:55.864
If it were up to you,
you would have picked Damon.

33:55.866 --> 33:58.066
(sighs)

33:58.068 --> 34:00.368
Yes.

34:00.370 --> 34:02.504
And you would've done it <i>knowing</i>

34:02.506 --> 34:05.073
that Enzo was the one fighting Sybil.

34:05.075 --> 34:08.109
The one risking his life to help us.

34:08.110 --> 34:10.110
- Yes.
- Let me ask you something.

34:10.112 --> 34:12.847
What <i>has</i> Damon done?

34:14.184 --> 34:16.551
Besides give up.

34:24.661 --> 34:27.829
She doesn't mean that. She's just upset.

34:27.831 --> 34:30.431
I'm gonna go stay with Bonnie tonight.

34:30.434 --> 34:31.766
She needs me.

34:31.768 --> 34:35.235
This has all been a lot for her.

34:35.237 --> 34:38.907
I hated us being on the opposite
side of the fight today.

34:38.909 --> 34:40.942
- I had to.
- I know.

34:40.944 --> 34:43.812
I know what you had to do.

34:43.813 --> 34:46.380
But I hated it.

34:48.051 --> 34:50.719
I hate all this.

34:53.290 --> 34:55.255
(sighs)

34:55.257 --> 34:57.792
I hate it, too.

35:14.578 --> 35:17.879
STEFAN: <i>Dear Elena,</i>

35:17.881 --> 35:19.180
<i>where to begin?</i>

35:19.182 --> 35:21.816
♪ ♪

35:34.231 --> 35:36.931
Looks like you could use that.

35:38.568 --> 35:41.269
- Thanks.
- Just trying to

35:41.271 --> 35:43.838
figure out a fresh new way
to deliver the same bad news.

35:43.840 --> 35:47.976
Well, I think your engagement
would qualify as good news.

35:47.978 --> 35:52.280
I'm pretty sure I forgot
to say congratulations

35:52.282 --> 35:54.916
- earlier.
- Thanks.

35:54.918 --> 35:56.317
Though I'm not sure today's how I wanted

35:56.319 --> 35:58.253
to spend the first day of it.

35:58.255 --> 35:59.888
Not to mention my best man just tried

35:59.890 --> 36:02.309
to take out a good chunk
of the wedding party.

36:02.334 --> 36:03.858
BARTENDER: Here you go.

36:03.860 --> 36:05.326
You can leave the bottle.

36:05.328 --> 36:06.961
Thanks.

36:06.963 --> 36:09.731
You know, I never had a brother.

36:09.733 --> 36:12.667
Uh, Damon was the closest thing.

36:12.669 --> 36:14.469
And I have to believe

36:14.471 --> 36:17.105
that if you have gotten him back before,

36:17.107 --> 36:19.974
there has got to be a way

36:19.976 --> 36:22.577
to do it again.

36:24.614 --> 36:27.248
I don't know. This is different.

36:27.250 --> 36:29.818
I've never seen him like this before.

36:29.820 --> 36:32.086
I really hoped that
when we put Sybil down,

36:32.088 --> 36:34.222
it'd break whatever
control she had over him.

36:34.224 --> 36:36.424
That he'd go back to being

36:36.426 --> 36:39.460
whatever Damon's
version of normal is again.

36:39.462 --> 36:42.197
<i>But somehow, some way,</i>

36:42.199 --> 36:43.898
<i>she still has ahold of him.</i>

36:43.900 --> 36:50.138
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh... ♪

36:50.140 --> 36:54.843
(high-pitched tone sounding)

36:57.247 --> 37:03.718
♪ Mm, mm, mm, mm... ♪

37:04.754 --> 37:07.322
(high-pitched tone sounding)

37:11.027 --> 37:14.863
♪ Hey, Joe ♪

37:14.865 --> 37:18.900
♪ I heard you shot your old lady down ♪

37:18.902 --> 37:22.003
♪ You shot her down to the ground ♪

37:22.005 --> 37:24.973
(whistling)

37:24.975 --> 37:28.610
♪ Yes, I did, I shot her ♪

37:28.612 --> 37:31.813
♪ You know I caught her messin'
'round town... ♪

37:31.815 --> 37:33.982
- I didn't know you cooked.
- Listen,

37:33.984 --> 37:35.750
you're gonna be here all the time,

37:35.752 --> 37:37.719
I am gonna need to get
some more pancake batter.

37:37.721 --> 37:40.622
Well, I'm only here because
you obviously want me here.

37:40.624 --> 37:42.457
I think you've seen the light, Damon.

37:42.459 --> 37:45.226
You know that true devotion
to me is the only way

37:45.228 --> 37:47.595
to save you from that
which you fear the most.

37:47.597 --> 37:49.931
But we still have a lot of work to do.

37:49.933 --> 37:51.399
Oh, yeah?

37:51.401 --> 37:53.301
What else is there to do?

37:53.303 --> 37:55.570
You still have too many attachments.

37:55.572 --> 37:57.906
Too many people willing to fight for you.

37:57.908 --> 38:00.174
They still believe you can be saved.

38:00.176 --> 38:02.043
We should work on that.

38:02.045 --> 38:04.445
What do they call it?

38:04.447 --> 38:07.081
Changing hearts and minds?

38:20.463 --> 38:23.865
♪ Hey, Joe... ♪

38:23.867 --> 38:25.266
Are you all right?

38:25.268 --> 38:28.236
♪ I heard you shot your mama down... ♪

38:28.238 --> 38:31.105
Damon?

38:32.842 --> 38:34.876
Lockwood.

38:34.878 --> 38:37.345
- ♪ Hey, Joe... ♪
- (Damon groans)

38:37.347 --> 38:40.114
Heard you haven't been yourself lately.

38:40.116 --> 38:42.350
Oh, I am who I've always been.

38:42.352 --> 38:44.752
Just got to keep proving it.

38:44.754 --> 38:47.755
Your fight's not with me, man.

38:47.757 --> 38:53.194
♪ Yes, I did, I shot her ♪

38:53.196 --> 38:55.697
♪ And I gave her the gun ♪

38:55.699 --> 38:57.098
♪ I shot her... ♪

38:57.100 --> 39:00.001
- (grunts)
- Nice hardware.

39:00.003 --> 39:01.636
(groans)

39:01.638 --> 39:03.972
Armory standard issue?

39:03.974 --> 39:08.009
You kill me, you can say
good-bye to everything.

39:08.011 --> 39:10.211
No one forgives you for this.

39:10.213 --> 39:12.146
I think we're way past that.

39:12.148 --> 39:13.715
(grunts)

39:13.717 --> 39:16.117
You have another option.

39:16.119 --> 39:17.685
Walk away.

39:17.687 --> 39:19.854
Fight whatever it is she wants you to do

39:19.856 --> 39:21.856
and get your life back.

39:21.858 --> 39:24.625
Walk away, Damon.

39:24.627 --> 39:26.627
Think about what you want
at the end of it all.

39:26.629 --> 39:30.198
- Think about <i>who</i> you want.
- That's the problem.

39:30.200 --> 39:32.100
I don't want any of it anymore.

39:32.102 --> 39:33.835
That's a lie. Is it?

39:33.837 --> 39:38.272
I wouldn't even know.

39:38.274 --> 39:41.309
Okay, then. Do it.

39:42.746 --> 39:45.580
If this is it, if this is the way I go out,

39:45.582 --> 39:47.415
then let me go out as the face

39:47.417 --> 39:49.817
that you can never erase from your brain.

39:49.819 --> 39:52.720
The face that reminds you,
to the end of time,

39:52.722 --> 39:55.056
of the moment you gave up.

39:55.058 --> 39:59.160
The moment you threw away
everything you've ever wanted...

39:59.162 --> 40:02.063
to be a siren's little bitch.

40:02.065 --> 40:04.512
Or maybe this'll be the
thing that wakes you up.

40:04.537 --> 40:06.817
And then maybe both our
lives will be worth something

40:06.842 --> 40:07.902
at the end of it all.

40:07.904 --> 40:09.604
So, go ahead.

40:09.606 --> 40:11.439
Do it.

40:11.441 --> 40:13.741
Tear me apart.

40:15.445 --> 40:19.514
♪ Hey, Joe ♪

40:19.516 --> 40:24.152
♪ You better run on down ♪

40:24.154 --> 40:25.547
♪ Good-bye, everybody ♪

40:25.572 --> 40:26.828
Do it!

40:28.124 --> 40:34.762
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh... ♪

40:34.764 --> 40:37.732
Damon?

40:42.806 --> 40:44.439
- (snarls)
- Damon, wait!

40:44.441 --> 40:46.774
(growling)

40:46.776 --> 40:48.543
(groaning)

40:57.921 --> 41:00.221
♪ Ah, ah, ah. ♪

